You can get one from an NPC at the Nightgate Inn. It's also pretty easy to sprint past the animals in Bloated Man's Grotto to grab the enchanted one there.
That's a pretty common bug with the thrall spells. I've fixed it by casting a cloak spell. If that doesn't work I've seen recommendations saying that being sent to jail will fix it. 
Are you using a follower? Having a follower seems to interfere with sneak attack bonuses a lot of the time.
You can start Dawnguard as a vampire. They won't start turning you away until a couple of missions in (if you stick with their half of the quest line). 
Yeah,  you need to be a pretty specialized character to find it useful. It's just an unusual enough item that it's worth knowing about. 

The way it increases magicka regen is unique. It modifies a different value than the other magicka regen enchantments. [This write up explains it better than I can](http://theskyrimblog.ning.com/group/glitches/forum/topics/let-s-investigate-the-ring-of-the-erudite?commentId=6452022%3AComment%3A1297911&amp;groupId=6452022%3AGroup%3A277857). 
You pretty much summed things up. One thing worth pointing out is that one of the rings you can get as a vampire has a unique effect that some mage builds might find very useful (the Ring of the Erudite).
